North Korea absolutely refuses unilateral disarmament without trust
North Korea's foreign minister told the UN on Saturday that maintaining sanctions was exacerbating the country's distrust of the US, which would under such circumstances refuse absolutely to give up its nuclear weapons unilaterally.
